review_text: I cannot use language to speak highly of all the courses Eden has created, it is not just the content, also his passion, as well as his vision for all those things gonna go. Not worth buying. The course uses an outdated version of LangGraph, and most examples and projects are directly taken from the documentation. The author claims this is an advanced course not intended for beginners, yet he frequently repeats himself and spends too much time covering LangChain basics that could be skipped. Every project starts with an identical setup video—why not make a single video for that instead of repeating the same process for each project? The course description advertises 6 hours of content, but in reality, only 3-4 hours consist of actual material, mostly taken from the documentation. I wouldn’t recommend this course; you’re better off investing your time in reading the official documentation instead.

I'm deeply grateful for the opportunity to explore the LangGraph course, "Develop LLM Powered AI Agents with LangGraph," designed to build real-world LLM AI agents swiftly and efficiently using Python. This course, a bestseller updated as recently as September 2024, is expertly crafted to offer comprehensive and engaging content and meaningful, real-world examples that enhance learning. The inclusion of an interactive class Discord server adds a dynamic dimension, allowing for real-time discussions and collaborations in multiple languages, including English and French. I appreciate the meticulous effort put into making this course accessible and enriching, paving the way for learners like myself to thrive in AI development. Thank you, Eden, for such a well-structured and insightful learning journey!

This course is an incredible journey into the power of LangGraph for building advanced LLM agent applications. The continuous updates and support from the instructor make this course even more valuable. If you have a background in Python and software engineering, this course will take your skills to the next level. Highly recommended for professionals looking to push the boundaries of AI development!

This is a very good starting course on LangGraph. It assumes knowledge of LangChain, and the instructor is quite explicit on that. The course is fast paces and you will need to pause many times either to catch up with the code or just digest the content. It is a very good starting point on more advanced material. Very good job and very well made and put together nicely. There are a few hickups like missing dependencies, but it is nothing that the student should be troubled by - as we said, this course is meant for people with at basic langchain knowledge. The only logical step after this course is to just dive in to developing and documentation. I am overall very happy with this course and kudos to the instructor for a job well done.
